article.headline: Liberty 83, N.C.-Asheville 54
article.story: LYNCHBURG, Va. (AP) -- Anthony Smith led five Liberty players in double figures with 18 points and the Flames used a big second half to coast past the University of North Carolina-Asheville 83-54 on Saturday night, handing the Big South-leading Bulldogs their first league loss. Vincent James gave UNC Asheville a 39-38 lead on a layup with 17:16 left in the game before the Flames went on a 13-2 run to take control. Liberty outscored the Bulldogs 52-25 in the second half. Alex McLean added 13 points and 10 rebounds while B.J. Jenkins scored 13 for Liberty (13-11, 5-4), which remained unbeaten in 11 games at home. TeeJay Bannister added 12 points and Jeremy Anderson scored 10. Reid Augst led UNC Asheville (18-5, 7-1) with 12 points and Sean Smith had 11. Leading scorer Bryan Smithson was limited to six points, more than 11 under his average, on 2-of-11 shooting. He was held to single digits for only the third time this season. UNC Asheville's 7-foot-7 Kenny George, the nation's tallest player, didn't play.
